<FeaturePage
  title="File Sync"
  description="Binary assets replicated alongside your data. Chunked, resumable, and offline-first."
  badge="Core · Library"
  activePath="/features"
>
  <p>
    Attach files to any record and sp00ky syncs them the same way it syncs your data — chunked,
    deduplicated, and resumable. Uploads continue in the background, resume after a disconnect,
    and stream straight through to the cloud vault when connected.
  </p>
  <p>
    Reads come from a local cache first, so images, audio, and docs render instantly even offline.
  </p>
  <h2>Capabilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Chunked transfers with content-addressed storage.</li>
    <li>Resumable uploads survive network drops and reloads.</li>
    <li>Offline-first reads with a tunable local cache.</li>
    <li>End-to-end encryption when paired with the Shared Vault.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
